        <div class="example">
            <p class="Example-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #5308be;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Example &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">Set the fields like this:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="Emphasis">Find </span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <img src="../../../../Images/Shared/Co-Fl-Li/Interface/Icons/Inline-Formatting-ico.png" alt="" title="" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> Inline Formatting</li>
                        <li>
                            <p>color: #ff0000; font-style: italic;</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><span class="Emphasis">Replace/Action </span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <img src="../../../../Images/Shared/Co-Fl-Li/Interface/Icons/Remove-Inline-Formatting-ico.png" alt="" title="" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> Remove Inline Formatting</li>
                        <li>
                            <p>color: #ff0000;</p>
                            <div class="note">
                                <p class="Note-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #fdc80b;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">If we had wanted to remove all of the inline formatting (not just some of it), we would have re-entered <span class="TypedEntry">color: #ff0000; font-style: italic;</span> here.</p>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><span class="Emphasis">Find in </span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>(documents in the same folder)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><span class="Emphasis">File types </span>
